    "reasoning": "To implement the Mealy-type finite state machine that recognizes the sequence '101', we need to define three states. The states can be represented as: S0 (start), S1 (received '1'), and S2 (received '10'). When the sequence '101' is detected, the output z should be asserted. The reset is asynchronous and active-low. The FSM operates on the positive edge of the clock. We'll use a Moore-style encoding approach where the current state determines the output and the next state is determined by the current state and the input. We'll ensure all signals are declared as logic. The states are defined using localparam for clarity. The reset logic should properly initialize the state after reset. For the combinational logic determining the next state and output, we will use always @(*) blocks. Since this is a Mealy machine, the output depends on both the present state and the input. To avoid syntax errors, we must ensure proper declaration and usage of signals, especially regarding bit indexing and concatenation.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input aresetn,\n    input x,\n    output z\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam S0 = 2'b00;\n    localparam S1 = 2'b01;\n    localparam S2 = 2'b10;\n\n    // State register\n    logic [1:0] state, next_state;\n\n    // Sequential logic for state register\n    always @(posedge clk or negedge aresetn) begin\n        if (!aresetn)\n            state <= S0;\n        else\n            state <= next_state;\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state and output\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            S0: begin\n                if (x)\n                    next_state = S1;\n                else\n                    next_state = S0;\n                z = 1'b0;\n            end\n            S1: begin\n                if (x)\n                    next_state = S1;\n                else\n                    next_state = S2;\n                z = 1'b0;\n            end\n            S2: begin\n                if (x)\n                    next_state = S1;\n                else\n                    next_state = S0;\n                z = 1'b1;\n            end\n        endcase\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
